    "summary": [
      "The Paris Agreement, adopted in December 2015, aims to limit global warming to 1.5°C above pre-industrial levels, but current global average temperatures in 2024 are dangerously close to this threshold, according to the IPCC Sixth Assessment Report.",
      "Global CO₂ emissions reached a record 37.4 gigatons in 2023, despite growth in renewable energy sectors in countries like Germany, China, and the United States, while fossil fuel consumption remains high, particularly in South and Southeast Asia.",
      "The European Union has cut emissions by 32% since 1990, but countries like Brazil, under President Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva, face criticism for Amazon deforestation, and India's net-zero target of 2070 is considered too late by many.",
      "The upcoming COP30 summit in Belém, Brazil, in November 2025, will test international resolve, with a need for more aggressive 2035 targets and political will to achieve the goals of the Paris Agreement, despite optimism in the renewable energy sector which saw solar power capacity surpass 2 terawatts in 2024."
    ],
